Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
modifyBudget(25.10)                                        modifyBudget(25.10)

Name
       modifyBudget  -  Modifies  budgets after they have been saved using the
       saveTimingBudget command

Syntax
       modifyBudget

       {-ptn <partitionName> | -inst <instanceName>}

       -file <fileName>

       [-setup | -hold]

       [-view <viewName>]

       [-help]

       Modifies budgets after they have been saved using the  saveTimingBudget
       command.  To  modify budgets, you must create an input budget file con-
       taining constraints that look  like  an  SDC  file.  It  only  supports
       set_input_delay  and  set_output_delay  constraints. The clock names in
       these constraints are same as the ones in the  generated  budget  file.
       You can provide a bus name instead of a pin name to apply the same bud-
       get to all pins of the bus.

       To  use modifyBudget, you must specify the following command before de-
       riveTimingBudget:

       setBudgetingMode -reportOrModifyBudget true

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each modifyBudget parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man modifyBudget

       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the input budget  file  containing  manual
              budgets.

       -hold  Specifies to modify the hold information.

       -inst <instanceName>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance for which manual
              budgets are to be applied.

       -ptn <partitionName>
              Specifies the name of the partition for which manual budgets are
              to be applied.

       -setup Specifies to modify the setup information.

       -view <viewName>
              Modifies  the  budget for the specified view. If you derived the
              timing budget in MMMC mode (default), this parameter is required
              to modify the budget.

Example
       The following command modifies the budget data for the instance inst1:

       modifyBudget -inst inst1 -file mod_inst

Related Information
       The "Modifying Budgets" section in the Timing Budgeting chapter of  the
       User Guide document.

